ac/Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Action/Defs.lean#L355-L360","name":"VAdd.comp.isScalarTower","line":355,"kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Action/Defs.html#VAdd.comp.isScalarTower","doc":"Given a tower of additive actions `M → α → β`, if we use `SMul.comp` to pull back both of\n`M`'s actions by a map `g : N → M`, then we obtain a new tower of scalar actions `N → α → β`.\n\nThis cannot be an instance because it can cause infinite loops whenever the `SMul` arguments\nare still metavariables."},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Action/Defs.html#VAdd.comp.isScalarTower\"><span class=\"name\">VAdd</span>.<span class=\"name\">comp</span>.<span class=\"name\">isScalarTower</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{M : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{N : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_6}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{β : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_7}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#VAdd\">VAdd</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#VAdd\">VAdd</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\